This paper is likely to belong to the sub-category of cs.LG (Machine Learning) as it proposes a new optimization algorithm for building deep learning models. It may also belong to cs.CV (Computer Vision) as deep learning models are widely used in computer vision tasks. Additionally, it could be categorized under cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) as optimization algorithms are a crucial component of AI. It may also fall under cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) as the paper focuses on optimization algorithms for neural networks. Finally, it could be categorized under cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) as it proposes a new algorithm for stochastic optimization.
